modules.description: This module handles HTTP response decompression and header manipulation for Cohttp. It provides `decompress` to process compressed response bodies based on the `content-encoding` header, supporting gzip and deflate, and `update_header` to ensure appropriate `accept-encoding` headers are set. Use it when consuming HTTP APIs that return compressed data or when preparing requests to negotiate compression.

This module provides functions to compress and decompress string data using the Deflate or Gzip algorithms. It supports streaming by operating on string chunks, enabling efficient handling of large response bodies without loading the entire content into memory. Concrete use cases include processing HTTP response bodies on the fly or writing decompressed data directly to a file.

This module provides a configuration value `cfg` that integrates with `ptime` for time-related operations. It is designed to work with `js_of_ocaml` by linking against `ptime.clock.js`, enabling accurate time handling in JavaScript environments. Use this module when you need a preconfigured time setup that works seamlessly across native and JavaScript targets.
